I"1<p>This example contains a LoRa duplex code to exchange GPS data between 2 nodes of the ESP32-based T-Beam by Xinyuan LilyGO version <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">T22_V1.1, 20191212</code>. After exchanging the GPS data, it will display its own latitude-longitude as well as the Haversine distance between the 2 notes on the OLED display.</p>

<p>Use this code with <a href="lora-duplex-b-gps-esp32-t-beam">duplex b</a>.</p>

<div class="language-c highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="n">byte</span> <span class="n">localAddress</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mh">0xAA</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="n">byte</span> <span class="n">destination</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mh">0xBB</span><span class="p">;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>4 types of information are shown on the OLED display:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Local nodeâ€™s latitude, longitude pair</li>
  <li>Last time since the local node had a GPS fix</li>
  <li>Haversine distance with the peer node</li>
  <li>Last time since both the local and peer node could get GPS fix around the same time enough to get a valid Haversine distance</li>
</ol>

